cots along with bed frames and bed rails innerspring mattress components in  harry m cornell jr jp leggett’s grandson was elected president and ceo of the company taking over for his father who was mr leggett’s soninlaw the company’s total sales in  were approximately  million from three states – kentucky texas and missouri determining the course and future of the company became management’s primary objective following an extensive evaluation of the company and its potential mr cornell and his management partners concluded that leggett  platt’s best opportunities for profitable growth lay in a strategy of specializing in manufacturing marketing and distributing a broad and growing line of components and related products first nationally and eventually on a worldwide basis key drivers of future sales and earnings would include aggressive internal growth initiatives coupled with an active and ongoing acquisition program jp leggetts original bedspring and patent even greater success followed and leggett  platt became known as “the components people” leggett  platt stock was first traded over the counter in  twelve years later on june   top management was present in new york city to witness the stock’s first day listed on the new york stock exchange in  the company became part of the sp  index today leggett  platt has  manufacturing facilities in  countries timelineedit  joseph p leggett develops and patents the first successful spiral steel coil bedspring then forms a business partnership with cornelius b platt a blacksmith who operates the cd platt plow works plant in carthage missouri  leggett receives a patent for improvements on the coiled bedspring jp leggett and cb platt begin manufacturing coiled bedsprings at the platt plow works plant  the first factory and offices are built in carthage mo the workforce consists of the  partners and  employees harry platt a brother of cb platt opens a franchise factory in louisville kentucky  the partnership of jp leggett and cb platt is incorporated under the name “leggett  platt spring bed  manufacturing company”  leggett  platt begins to manufacture innerspring units at its carthage plant  leggett  platt survives world war ii by working on defense contracts  harry m cornell jr grandson of jp leggett becomes president and ceo he begins implementing a new corporate strategy to broaden the line of component products for the bedding and furniture industries expand geographically and offer compatible products directly to furniture stores  leggett  platt’s ipo initial public offering of  shares of stock at  per share and  million of convertible subordinated debentures occurs the stock is listed over the counter  leggett  platt stock is listed on the nasdaq and the company achieves more than  million in net earnings  leggett  platt exceeds the  million sales mark for the first time  construction begins on a new corporate headquarters outside carthage  leggett  platt is listed on the nyse new york stock exchange stock symbol leg  leggett celebrates  years of operation  revenues exceed  billion for the first time  leggett is included in the sp   new strategic direction announced in november  reset to strategic direction announced in september executive leadership past  presentedit executive years of service jp leggett  cb platt partnership – jp leggett – cb platt – jp leggett jr – fb williams – george s beimdiek sr – harry m cornell sr – harry m cornell jr – felix e wright – david s haffner – karl g glassman –present leg stockedit   leggett  platt ipo of  shares of stock at a price of  per share the stock is traded over the counter   leggetts stock is listed on the nasdaq   leggett is listed on the new york stock exchange trading under symbol leg history of stock splits may   for jan   for sept   for aug   for mar   for jun   for sept   for jun   for referencesedit  httpwwwleggettcomresidentialfurnishingshtm  httpwwwfundinguniversecomcompanyhistoriesleggettampplattinccompanyhistoryhtml  httpsfinanceyahoocomqprsleg external linksedit companies portal lps homepage business data for leggett  platt google finance yahoo finance reuters sec filings lp corporate overview lps adjustable beds homepage v t e mattress manufacturers bloom casper dorel endy sleep eve sleep helix sleep ikea king koil leesa sleep leggett  platt purple saatva sealy select comfort serta shifman simmons spring air tempurpedic thermarest tuft  needle retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleleggettplattoldid categories companies listed on the new york stock exchangemanufacturing companies based in missouristandard  poorshidden categories articles needing additional references from january all articles needing additional referencesall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from april  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages deutschpolski edit links this page was last edited on  may  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view leggett  platt  wikipedia leggett  platt from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from leggett  platt inc jump to navigation search this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed january  learn how and when to remove this template message leggett  platt type public traded as nyse leg sp  component industry residential bedding and furniture automotive seating industrial materials founded   years ago  headquarters carthage missouri united states key people karl g glassman president  ceo revenue  billion usd  operating income  million usd  net income  million usd  number of employees   website leggettcom leggett  platt lp based in carthage missouri is a diversified manufacturer and member of the sp  index that designs and produces various engineered components and products the firm was founded in  and consists of  business units  employeepartners and  manufacturing facilities located in  countriescitation needed contents  company segments  residential products  industrial products  furniture products  specialized products  leggett management  board of directors  company history  timeline  executive leadership past  present  leg stock  references  external links company segmentsedit residential productsedit leggett  platt provides a variety of components and machinery used by bedding manufacturers in the production and assembly of their finished products leggett  platt also produces and distributes carpet cushion for residential and commercial applications in addition they are a major distributor of geo components used in ground stabilization drainage protection erosion control and weed control industrial productsedit leggett  platt is a producer of drawn steel wire the companys three wire mills produce virtually all of the wire consumed by their other domestic business as well as supplying external customers much of the steel rod used to produce this wire is manufactured in leggett  platts own rod mill they also produce and distribute wire products for various industrial applications furniture productsedit leggett  platt is the worlds leading independent manufacturer of motion and other components for work and residential furniture in addition they produce select lines of privatelabel finished furniture they are also a leading supplier of adjustable beds and fashion bed products which are sold primarily to bedding retailers and other retail markets specialized productsedit leggett  platt is a designer and manufacturer of automotive seating support pneumatic and mechanical lumbar systems they are also a supplier of titanium nickel and stainless steel tubing to the aerospace industry it is a supplier of service van interiors used in commercial vehicles leggett managementedit as of january  senior corporate executives included karl g glassman president  ceo perry e davis evp  president residential  industrial products segments j mitchell dolloff evp  president furniture  specialized products segments matthew c flanigan evp  cfo david m desonier svp strategy and investor relations board of directorsedit director joined in position company robert e brunner  retired executive vp illinois tool works inc robert g culp iii  chairman culp inc r ted enloe iii  managing general partner  board chair balquita partners ltd manuel a fernandez  managing director si ventures matthew c flanigan  evp  cfo leggett  platt karl g glassman  president  ceo leggett  platt joseph w mcclanathan  retired president  ceo energizer household products division of energizer holdings judy c odom  retired chairman  ceo software spectrum inc phoebe a wood  principal companieswood company historyedit jp leggett cb platt in  in carthage missouri jp leggett developed a new type of bedspring consisting of single cone spring wire coils formed and interlaced then mounted on a wood slat base the bedspring could then be used as a base for the thenpopular cotton feather or horsehair mattresses needing expertise in manufacturing and production he recruited his soontobe brotherinlaw cb platt whose father owned and operated platt plow works into the partnership together they produced the components of their leggett  platt bedspring which was patented in  bedspring vs innerspring at the time of their invention bedsprings referred to coneshaped wire coiled springs attached to a wooden slat foundation used to support thenpopular mattresses these mattresses were typically made of horse hair corn husks cotton feathers or another soft material early bedsprings functioned similarly to todays box springs in their support of a mattress however box springs are rather rigid in structure while bedsprings provide a more flexible surface innersprings by contrast refer to the core system of wire springs that along with various types of foam and other padding materials comprise the insides of todays mattress the mattress is usually coupled with a box spring to create a sleep set innersprings can be coiled springs laced together continuous coil springs or individually encased springs that support a person sleeping on the mattress the carthage market for their new product was very limited to expand the market to a wider region mr platt and george leggett brother of j p leggett would load a horsedrawn wagon with bedsprings and travel to surrounding communities often to conserve space they would load the springs and slats separately into the wagon and assemble them in a store or on an adjacent sidewalk the partnership prospered and the business was incorporated in  the platt plow works the company built its first factory and offices in carthage in  the workforce at that time consisted of the two partners and five employees soon after completion of the carthage plant a second factory was built in louisville kentucky during the next  years three more factories were built demand for the company’s improved bedsprings was rising and a second plant was built in carthage in  the new much larger plant was located next to a railroad to allow for expanded shipments of products and supplies in  an additional factory was built in winchester kentucky which was subsequently consolidated with the louisville plant for some time texas had proven to be a main market outlet and in  a major factory was built in ennis texas by  leggett  platt consisted of  plants and  employees although available in various models and continuously improved upon bedsprings were practically the only product leggett  platt offered until  however in that year the company began to manufacture springs for innerspring mattresses which were relatively new products in the industry and growing in popularity thereafter the company slowly began to diversify its products within the bedding industry by producing rollaway beds and folding metal cots along with bed frames and bed rails innerspring mattress components in  harry m cornell jr jp leggett’s grandson was elected president and ceo of the company taking over for his father who was mr leggett’s soninlaw the company’s total sales in  were approximately  million from three states – kentucky texas and missouri determining the course and future of the company became management’s primary objective following an extensive evaluation of the company and its potential mr cornell and his management partners concluded that leggett  platt’s best opportunities for profitable growth lay in a strategy of specializing in manufacturing marketing and distributing a broad and growing line of components and related products first nationally and eventually on a worldwide basis key drivers of future sales and earnings would include aggressive internal growth initiatives coupled with an active and ongoing acquisition program jp leggetts original bedspring and patent even greater success followed and leggett  platt became known as “the components people” leggett  platt stock was first traded over the counter in  twelve years later on june   top management was present in new york city to witness the stock’s first day listed on the new york stock exchange in  the company became part of the sp  index today leggett  platt has  manufacturing facilities in  countries timelineedit  joseph p leggett develops and patents the first successful spiral steel coil bedspring then forms a business partnership with cornelius b platt a blacksmith who operates the cd platt plow works plant in carthage missouri  leggett receives a patent for improvements on the coiled bedspring jp leggett and cb platt begin manufacturing coiled bedsprings at the platt plow works plant  the first factory and offices are built in carthage mo the workforce consists of the  partners and  employees harry platt a brother of cb platt opens a franchise factory in louisville kentucky  the partnership of jp leggett and cb platt is incorporated under the name “leggett  platt spring bed  manufacturing company”  leggett  platt begins to manufacture innerspring units at its carthage plant  leggett  platt survives world war ii by working on defense contracts  harry m cornell jr grandson of jp leggett becomes president and ceo he begins implementing a new corporate strategy to broaden the line of component products for the bedding and furniture industries expand geographically and offer compatible products directly to furniture stores  leggett  platt’s ipo initial public offering of  shares of stock at  per share and  million of convertible subordinated debentures occurs the stock is listed over the counter  leggett  platt stock is listed on the nasdaq and the company achieves more than  million in net earnings  leggett  platt exceeds the  million sales mark for the first time  construction begins on a new corporate headquarters outside carthage  leggett  platt is listed on the nyse new york stock exchange stock symbol leg  leggett celebrates  years of operation  revenues exceed  billion for the first time  leggett is included in the sp   new strategic direction announced in november  reset to strategic direction announced in september executive leadership past  presentedit executive years of service jp leggett  cb platt partnership – jp leggett – 