ise the insides of todays mattress the mattress is usually coupled with a box spring to create a sleep set innersprings can be coiled springs laced together continuous coil springs or individually encased springs that support a person sleeping on the mattress the carthage market for their new product was very limited to expand the market to a wider region mr platt and george leggett brother of j p leggett would load a horsedrawn wagon with bedsprings and travel to surrounding communities often to conserve space they would load the springs and slats separately into the wagon and assemble them in a store or on an adjacent sidewalk the partnership prospered and the business was incorporated in  the platt plow works the company built its first factory and offices in carthage in  the workforce at that time consisted of the two partners and five employees soon after completion of the carthage plant a second factory was built in louisville kentucky during the next  years three more factories were built demand for the company’s improved bedsprings was rising and a second plant was built in carthage in  the new much larger plant was located next to a railroad to allow for expanded shipments of products and supplies in  an additional factory was built in winchester kentucky which was subsequently consolidated with the louisville plant for some time texas had proven to be a main market outlet and in  a major factory was built in ennis texas by  leggett  platt consisted of  plants and  employees although available in various models and continuously improved upon bedsprings were practically the only product leggett  platt offered until  however in that year the company began to manufacture springs for innerspring mattresses which were relatively new products in the industry and growing in popularity thereafter the company slowly began to diversify its products within the bedding industry by producing rollaway beds and folding metal cots along with bed frames and bed rails innerspring mattress components in  harry m cornell jr jp leggett’s grandson was elected president and ceo of the company taking over for his father who was mr leggett’s soninlaw the company’s total sales in  were approximately  million from three states – kentucky texas and missouri determining the course and future of the company became management’s primary objective following an extensive evaluation of the company and its potential mr cornell and his management partners concluded that leggett  platt’s best opportunities for profitable growth lay in a strategy of specializing in manufacturing marketing and distributing a broad and growing line of components and related products first nationally and eventually on a worldwide basis key drivers of future sales and earnings would include aggressive internal growth initiatives coupled with an active and ongoing acquisition program jp leggetts original bedspring and patent even greater success followed and leggett  platt became known as “the components people” leggett  platt stock was first traded over the counter in  twelve years later on june   top management was present in new york city to witness the stock’s first day listed on the new york stock exchange in  the company became part of the sp  index today leggett  platt has  manufacturing facilities in  countries timelineedit  joseph p leggett develops and patents the first successful spiral steel coil bedspring then forms a business partnership with cornelius b platt a blacksmith who operates the cd platt plow works plant in carthage missouri  leggett receives a patent for improvements on the coiled bedspring jp leggett and cb platt begin manufacturing coiled bedsprings at the platt plow works plant  the first factory and offices are built in carthage mo the workforce consists of the  partners and  employees harry platt a brother of cb platt opens a franchise factory in louisville kentucky  the partnership of jp leggett and cb platt is incorporated under the name “leggett  platt spring bed  manufacturing company”  leggett  platt begins to manufacture innerspring units at its carthage plant  leggett  platt survives world war ii by working on defense contracts  harry m cornell jr grandson of jp leggett becomes president and ceo he begins implementing a new corporate strategy to broaden the line of component products for the bedding and furniture industries expand geographically and offer compatible products directly to furniture stores  leggett  platt’s ipo initial public offering of  shares of stock at  per share and  million of convertible subordinated debentures occurs the stock is listed over the counter  leggett  platt stock is listed on the nasdaq and the company achieves more than  million in net earnings  leggett  platt exceeds the  million sales mark for the first time  construction begins on a new corporate headquarters outside carthage  leggett  platt is listed on the nyse new york stock exchange stock symbol leg  leggett celebrates  years of operation  revenues exceed  billion for the first time  leggett is included in the sp   new strategic direction announced in november  reset to strategic direction announced in september executive leadership past  presentedit executive years of service jp leggett  cb platt partnership – jp leggett – cb platt – jp leggett jr – fb williams – george s beimdiek sr – harry m cornell sr – harry m cornell jr – felix e wright – david s haffner – karl g glassman –present leg stockedit   leggett  platt ipo of  shares of stock at a price of  per share the stock is traded over the counter   leggetts stock is listed on the nasdaq   leggett is listed on the new york stock exchange trading under symbol leg history of stock splits may   for jan   for sept   for aug   for mar   for jun   for sept   for jun   for referencesedit  httpwwwleggettcomresidentialfurnishingshtm  httpwwwfundinguniversecomcompanyhistoriesleggettampplattinccompanyhistoryhtml  httpsfinanceyahoocomqprsleg external linksedit compan